What started as an old bungalow home built in 1919, transformed into the beautiful establishment it is today. Capturing the historic Mount Dora vibes, the original owners of the restaurant choose to keep the original 1919 home intact and made it the centerpiece of the restaurant. The original living room and dining room of the home is used as dining areas for small and large parties. Enjoy outside dining on the deck or tiki bar overlooking Lake Dora and the setting sun. For a more intimate experience, dine inside surrounded by beautiful windows that offer a spectacular view of the lake. The open kitchen is our “heart-of-the-house.” Our menu consists of Southern Florida dishes with a focus on utilizing fresh, local ingredients. Hours of Operation Monday, Wednesday, Thursday: 11:30AM-3:00PM / 5:00PM-9:00PM Tuesday: 5:00PM-9:00PM Friday & Saturday: 11:30AM-3:00PM / 5:00PM-10:00PM Sunday: 11:00AM-3:00 PM / 5:00PM-9:00PM Happy Hour Voted Best Happy Hour in Mount Dora Buzz’s Best of Mount Dora poll! Monday: ALL DAY Tuesday: 5PM-7PM Wednesday-Friday: 4PM-7PM Our Core Values Our service mission is to deliver hospitality with grace, warmth, and compassion. Our culinary mission is to execute fresh, distinctive takes on modern cuisine with homage to the culture that make up today’s traditions. The room can fit up to 40 people at multiple tables or up to 20 at one long table. We also have other semi-private rooms connected to the main room that can in total accommodate 80+ guests. We have hosted countless wedding rehearsal and reception dinners, graduation dinners, business meetings, anniversary parties, birthday parties, and other successful outings. We are also able to offer the entire restaurant for certain occasions; no event is too large or too small! View one of our Private Group menus that showcase a cost effective limited menu perfect for any gathering. We can also design a more personal menu specific for your needs, or you can order directly from our regular menu to keep your options open! Contact our Event Coordinator by email at samanthag@piscesrisingdining.com or by phone at 352-385-2669. We recommend completing an inquiry form below so we can gather preliminary questions about your event to get the booking process started.
